PART 5: THE CROSSING
Time: 30-40 Minutes
 Goal: Use the Writ to bluff past the Thalmor or fight through the checkpoint
SCENE 1: THE RETURN TO THE BRIDGE
READ ALOUD:
"You return to the White River Bridge as the sun begins to set. The Thalmor checkpoint looks even more imposing in the fading light—the magical ward glows with a soft golden luminescence, and torches have been lit along the barricades.
The same Justiciar Captain who turned you away earlier stands at the checkpoint, flanked by two robed wizards. Behind him, you can see more Justiciars in formation—a shield wall of golden armor and cold Altmer faces.
And standing slightly apart from the others, watching the checkpoint with analytical patience, is a High Elf in more elaborate robes. His armor is ornate, marked with the symbols of high rank. His eyes miss nothing.
This is Third Emissary Rulindil. You've heard the name before—a master interrogator from the Thalmor Embassy, known for his ability to extract truth from lies like a surgeon removing rot from flesh."
THE INTERACTION
The party must present the Forged Imperial Writ to Justiciar Talmor.
Justiciar Talmor: (taking the document, examining it) "An Imperial Writ. Let me see..."
(He studies the seal, the signature, the wording. This takes an uncomfortably long time.)
This is the moment Rulindil steps forward.
Third Emissary Rulindil: "Allow me, Captain."
(He takes the Writ from Talmor's hands and studies it with the intensity of a hawk examining prey.)
THE BLUFF
The party must make a Very Hard (-6) Guile (Deception) check.
Modifiers:
If Hirt is visible and Rulindil noticed him earlier: Additional -2 penalty (he's suspicious)
If the party has a good cover story prepared: +2 bonus
If the party seems nervous or evasive: -2 penalty
The Questions:
Rulindil will ask pointed questions designed to expose lies:
"This Writ is signed by Legate Rikke. Where did you receive it?"
"What business do you have in Whiterun Hold?"
"These seals are freshly applied. Why was this document issued so recently?"
(If Hirt is present) "You. The Nord. Step forward. What is your name and occupation?"
The party must answer convincingly. Have them roleplay their responses. Judge each answer and apply bonuses or penalties as appropriate.
SUCCESS: SUSPICIOUS BUT ALLOWED
Rulindil: (after a long, uncomfortable pause) "This Writ appears... authentic. Though I have concerns about its provenance."
(He hands it back)
Rulindil: "You may pass. But know this—if I discover this document was obtained through fraud or deception, the Dominion has a very long memory. You will be found. And you will answer for it."
(He signals to the wizards. The magical ward shimmers and opens a narrow passage.)
The party can cross. As they do, Rulindil watches them with cold, calculating eyes.
FAILURE: EXPOSED
Rulindil: (his voice cutting through any attempted explanation) "This is a crude forgery. The seal is accurate, but the wording is wrong—Legate Rikke does not use this phrasing in official documents. I have read hundreds of her writs."
(He steps back, hand moving to his sword)
Rulindil: "You are attempting to cross an Aldmeri checkpoint using fraudulent Imperial documentation. This is a violation of the White-Gold Concordat. Seize them."
Combat begins.

THE BREAKOUT FIGHT
This is not a fight to the death. The goal is to escape, not to win.
THE OBJECTIVE
The party must destroy the Ward Stone—a magical obelisk behind the checkpoint that powers the barrier. Once it's destroyed, the ward collapses and they can run through.
Ward Stone:
HP: 30
DR: 6 (Magical Stone)
Location: 30 feet behind the first line of Justiciars
THE ENEMY FORCE
Third Emissary Rulindil (Boss)
See full stat block below
He will use Silence on the party's mages immediately
He fights to capture, not kill (initially)
4x Thalmor Justiciars (Shield Wall)
See stat block below
They form a defensive line blocking access to the Ward Stone
2x Thalmor Wizards (Artillery)
See stat block below
They cast ranged Destruction spells from behind the Justiciars
TACTICS
Round 1: Rulindil casts Silence on the party's primary spellcaster. The Justiciars advance in formation. The Wizards begin casting.
Round 2-3: The Justiciars attempt to grapple and restrain party members. Rulindil focuses on whoever is trying to reach the Ward Stone.
Round 4+: If the Ward Stone is destroyed, Rulindil will attempt one last Paralyze to stop the party's escape, then let them go rather than risk his entire unit in pursuit.
ENVIRONMENTAL FACTORS
The Bridge: The stone bridge is wide but has low railings. Characters can be pushed off (15-foot drop into fast-moving water—8 damage and swept downstream)
The Barricades: Provide half-cover (+2 DR against ranged attacks)
The Ward: Characters can't pass through until the Ward Stone is destroyed

